1929. Concatenation of Array

Given an integer array nums of length n, you want to create an array ans of length 2n where ans[i] == nums[i] and ans[i + n] == nums[i] for 0 <= i < n (0-indexed).

Specifically, ans is the concatenation of two nums arrays.

Return the array ans.

Example 1:

Input: nums = [1,2,1]
Output: [1,2,1,1,2,1]
Explanation: The array ans is formed as follows:
- ans = [nums[0],nums[1],nums[2],nums[0],nums[1],nums[2]]
- ans = [1,2,1,1,2,1]

Solution:
class Solution {
    public int[] getConcatenation(int[] nums) {
        int n = nums.length;
        int start = 0;
       int[] ans = new int[n *2]; 

       for (int i =0; i < n; i++){
           ans[i] = nums[i];
       }
       for(int j =n; j < ans.length; j++){ //start at length of nums, and go till end of ans array, at first index outside of nums.length, repeat the nums array
           ans[j] = nums[start];
           start++;  //increment start variable so that it can add the next element in the nums array
       }
       return ans;
    }//ending method 
}
